  <summary date="2022-06-13T18:03:26Z" status="Introduced in House">Supreme Court Police Parity Act of 2022

This bill grants the Marshal of the Supreme Court and the Supreme Court Police the authority to protect any member of the immediate family of the Chief Justice, any Associate Justice, or any officer of the Supreme Court if the Marshal determines that such protection is necessary.</summary>
